replies.content: Thanks for the invite James, it looks like an exciting platform for people to be able to connect. One question, is there a way to search by skills tag? I saw the top skill listed on the dashboard, but didn't see a skills filter (must be missing something). Thanks

Hi Stacy, I saw your question come through but there was a notification glitch (and apparently it didn't show up here either! Welcome to Beta :) All should be fixed now. To answer your question, you can filter by skill by either clicking on a skill (in the top skills list) or simply typing something in the search field, such as 'Angular'. I welcome any feedback you have!

Ah, I was hoping to have a full list of skills tags to click on, or a filter in the sidebar, instead of typing in one that wasn't a tag, such as UX instead of User Experience or Testing vs Tester. Just IMO but when there are tags it sets the expectations to be able to use them for filtering. I know you have the Top Skills, but I noticed when I was browsing that I was expecting to be able to get to a list of all the registered skills.
It's a pretty long list (1200+ I believe) but I could possibly do an auto-complete or something, but then you'd still have to start typing one in before it completed.

...if you're interested in my feedback... When I logged back in after signing up, I was taken to my profile page and then I wanted to get to the dashboard. So I clicked on the Startup logo, assuming that it would act like the home link you see on websites. But this brought up the dashboard with no info in it (i.e. 0 people). So then I started moving down the sidebar. Clicked on the big bold Bend, OR and still 0 people and companies, clicked on People, etc. and didn't see detailed results until I clicked on BendTech. My expectation would've been to have seen info earlier or even been taken to the dashboard first. I realize that you'll be rolling this out to multiple communities, but perhaps a default location? Just my impressions.
Yep, you found a bug! It is supposed to work like you suggested, but I changed something recently and apparently screwed it up. I'm looking into it now.. thanks!
Fixed now :) Fortunately it was only an issue if clicking the logo.
